            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#AA">
                <p>To Gaius Pausculanus Maximus, son of Gaius, of tribe Quirina, aedile, quinquennalis, prefect for administering justice, quaestor of the alimenta,
                   flamen Augustalis, this man gave for the honour of [being elected to] quinquennial office, a spectacle of gladiators for three days, and [executed] four criminals,
                   and the same for the honour of [being elected as] curator of grain. He lived for 34 years and 4 days. Gaius Pausculanus Rufus, his most loving son, erected this.
                   This monument shall not pass to a buyer, but in such a way that it is permitted that right of passage, right of access, and right to the area around the tomb may be
                   permitted to me and my descendants. In depth, 70 feet; on the front, 12 feet.
                </p>
